#heading(level: 1, outlined: false)[Acknowledgements]

I would like to begin by expressing my deepest gratitude to my family. Completing a dissertation, and a university degree as a whole, is a massive undertaking, and I absolutely could not have reached this finish line without your unwavering support and encouragement from day one. Thank you for always believing in me, for your endless patience during the most stressful weeks of coding and writing, and for always being in my corner. Your support has been my foundation throughout this entire journey, and I am endlessly grateful for everything you do.

A special shoutout goes to the Computer Science Society (CSS), without it, I wouldn't have met so many of the amazing people I now call friends. To all my friends, thank you for keeping me sane over the course of this project and throughout my time at university. Whether it was providing much-needed distractions when I needed to step away from the screen, letting me bounce half-formed ideas off you, or just patiently listening to me talk endlessly about tabletop games, Unity bugs, and cognitive load theory for months on end, I truly appreciate it. Thank you for the laughs, the breaks, and for making this whole experience enjoyable despite the heavy workload.

I also want to give a special mention to my course lead, Khaled Bachour, who has honestly been the best throughout this entire process. Whenever I reached out with questions or guidance, he always responded incredibly quickly and provided exactly the feedback I needed to keep moving forward. Having that kind of reliable, fast support made a world of difference.

Finally, I would like to acknowledge my supervisor, Themis Papaioannou. Thank you for your time and the guidance you provided during the formative stages of this project. I appreciate the initial feedback and direction that helped get this research off the ground and oriented toward its final goals.